        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 PW/9–1145: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-11">September 11,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received September 18—6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–1067. American Interests—Japan. Foreign Office note, September 7, states Swiss
                    Minister Tokyo had lengthy discussion with Japanese Foreign Office with regard
                    contents Department’s 1992, June 8.<note n="48" xml:id="d271fn1">See bracketed
                        note, <ref target="#pg_342">p. 342</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Swiss Minister states it would seem that Japanese authorities made every effort
                    to give proper food to internees Shanghai region despite considerable
                    difficulties they encountered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
